Developing a large utility Customer Information System (CIS) involves significant risk due to broad scope, mission-critical functionality, and technical complexity. Many consider these characteristics best suited for a traditional development approach. Southern California Gas (SCG), like Brooklyn Union Gas, has pursued an object-oriented approach for their CIS. SCG and Andersen Consulting are near the end of a three year development effort. We plan to meet the originally scheduled conversion date of September 1995. In this paper we discuss the key management risks encountered, strategic decisions made, and lessons learned in three areas: 0 Software Architecture l Macro Process and Team Organization l Development Methodology